<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TVM3.1.7">
<l>vāḻttuvār palarāka niṉṉuḷḷē nāṉmukaṉai</l>
<l>mūḻttanī rulakellām paṭaiyeṉṟu mutalpaṭaittāy</l>
<l>kēḻtta cīraraṉ mutalāk kiḷarteyva māykiḷarntu</l>
<l>cūḻttamarar tutittāluṉ ṭolpukaḻmā cūṇātē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>While there are many who praise [you], in your mind your created</l>
<l>the four-faced one first, telling [him] “create the world [and] the water that engulfs [it]!”</l>
<l>If the immortals with Hara of lustrous excellence as the first emerge as bright gods</l>
<l>[and] praise [you] all around, will not your ancient fame absorb the stains?<note>Parallels for the controversial mācūṇam: Poykai 82.3, TVM 1.5.4 uṉ perumai mācu-uṇātō māyōṉē.</note> </l>

      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
